import React, { useState } from 'react'; import { Container, Paper, Typography, Table, TableBody, TableCell, TableContainer, TableHead, TableRow, Button, Chip, Stack, } from '@mui/material'; interface Employee { id: string; account: string; position: string; department: string; hireDate: string; status: 'Active' | 'Inactive'; } const initialEmployees: Employee[] = [ { id: 'EMP001', account: 'admin@example.com', position: 'Developer', department: 'Engineering', hireDate: '1/1/2025', status: 'Active', }, { id: 'EMP002', account: 'user@example.com', position: 'Designer', department: 'Marketing', hireDate: '2/1/2025', status: 'Active', }, ]; const Employees = () => { const [employees] = useState(initialEmployees); return ( EMPLOYEES Employee ID Account Position Department Hire Date Status Actions {employees.map((employee) => ( {employee.id} {employee.account} {employee.position} {employee.department} {employee.hireDate} ))}
); }; export default Employees;
